{"about_the_game":"<p class=\"bb_paragraph\">In this <strong>nightmare simulator</strong>, you will dive into the dreams of the character Yuha, experiencing her emotions and fears, and uncovering her story through objects and memories. The game <strong>is based on the real dreams</strong> of the developer Yulia Kozhemyako, with Yuha as her virtual counterpart.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\"></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\"><strong>The first episode, \u00abCatastrophe\u00bb</strong>, focuses on the concept of home, its loss and finding a home in another dimension. In this episode, the creator explores her views on responsibility, relationships with parents and homeland, and attitudes toward possessions and material values \u2014 accumulating, letting go, and their virtualization.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\"></p><h2 class=\"bb_tag\"><strong>The game doesn't tell a story about a dream; it is played and feels like a dream</strong></h2><p class=\"bb_paragraph\"></p><ul class=\"bb_ul\"><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\">Immerse yourself in <strong>familiar nightmare scenarios</strong>: apocalypse, returning to a childhood home, endless running away, and disappearing staircases. </p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\">Experience a true nightmare with <strong>slow motion, loss of voice, and dreams within dreams</strong>.</p></li></ul><p class=\"bb_paragraph\"></p><h2 class=\"bb_tag\"><strong>The \u00abflip side\u00bb of the 3D world and glitches</strong></h2><p class=\"bb_paragraph\"></p><ul class=\"bb_ul\"><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\"><strong>The Wireframe World</strong>: explore Yuha's subconscious through a wireframe view, usually unavailable to players. You'll see through walls, observe the level's structure, and uncover the secrets of the main character through the mysteries of the game!</p></li></ul><p class=\"bb_paragraph\"></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\"><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1457940/extras/forSteam_wireframes.gif?t=1730286749\" /></p><ul class=\"bb_ul\"><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\"><strong>Glitches</strong> are part of the world and gameplay. You're in for a unique experience: playing with altered fields of view, mismatches between the visible graphical layer and the physical dimension of the game environment, discrepancies between what seems real and what feels real, and getting stuck in textures.</p></li></ul><p class=\"bb_paragraph\"></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\"><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1457940/extras/forSteam_glitches.gif?t=1730286749\" /></p><h2 class=\"bb_tag\"><strong>Story</strong></h2><p class=\"bb_paragraph\"></p><ul class=\"bb_ul\"><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\">Based on real dreams.</p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\">Explore objects and the environment and objects to learn more about the main character.</p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\">Yuha's thoughts will accompany you on this adventure.</p></li></ul><p class=\"bb_paragraph\"></p><h2 class=\"bb_tag\"><strong>Gameplay</strong></h2><p class=\"bb_paragraph\"></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\">You'll need to quickly collect items, find your way out of the house, dodge bullets (or let them hit their target), find your cat among many others, and more. But the main objective is to understand the structure of this world and learn how to interact with it to complete the journey and uncover the full story.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\"></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\">The game will be released episodically, with each episode focusing on a specific theme. The first episode, \u00abCatastrophe\u00bb, consists of over 10 dream-levels. Each dream is a separate adventure, but all the dreams are connected by a common storyline.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\"></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\"><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1457940/extras/forSteam_allIn.gif?t=1730286749\" /></p><p class=\"bb_par